This privacy policy (the “Privacy Policy”) constitutes an agreement between you and Procare Software, LLC and its affiliates, corporate parent(s), and subsidiaries (collectively “Procare”, “us”, “our,” or “we”). Procare is dedicated to protecting your privacy. This policy describes what Procare collects, and how we use, protect, and disclose information collected and created during your use of this Procare website.
YOUR ACCEPTANCE
By continuing to use this site, you agree to this policy.
WHAT WE COLLECT
When you visit our site, we automatically collect:
The website URL you came from.
The start time and duration of your visit.
The pages you visited and your journey through our site.
Your IP address and geolocation.
The browser, device type and operating system of your computer.
We also collect personally identifiable information you voluntarily provide when you submit a form, make a request, register for, or log into our site.
HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION
When you supply information about yourself for a specific purpose, we use the information only for that purpose and to manage the internal operations and security of our site consistent with the Terms of Use governing this site and this Privacy Policy. Such purpose may include the disclosure of your information to unaffiliated companies/vendors where necessary to and for the limited purpose of processing your request, processing a transaction authorized by you, or providing you with products or services.
When you voluntarily submit information to us (such as submitting a Demo Request), you are agreeing to receive marketing email, phone communications and print collateral from Procare Software. You may opt-out from receiving marketing email at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link in any email you receive from us.
At times we may ask you for contact information or conduct online surveys to better understand your needs, so that we can provide you with a customized experience. If we wish to use this information other than as set forth in this Privacy Policy, we will let you know at the time of collection.
USE OF COOKIES
Our site use cookies, which are small files stored on your computer that contain information about your visits (see “What We Collect” above). By using cookies, we can personalize our site to enhance your online experience and measure things, such as the total number of visits, average time spent on the site, number of pages viewed, and how people reach our site. You can prevent cookies by configuring your browser to reject them or to notify you when a cookie is being placed on your computer.
SECURITY AND ACCESS TO YOUR INFORMATION
We will take commercially reasonable steps to safeguard your information from unauthorized access. When you submit information through our site, it is protected both online and offline. We maintain physical, electronic, and procedural security measures to safeguard your non-public personal information. Access to such information is restricted to employees who are subject to an Employee Restrictive Covenant Policy.
DISCLOSURE REQUIRED BY LAW
We may be required to disclose non-public personal information about you to comply with certain federal, state and local laws or government regulations, or when we believe that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights and/or comply with a judicial proceeding, court order, or legal process served on our site. In these circumstances, we will use reasonable efforts to disclose only the information required to be disclosed.
