CALIFORNIA RESIDENTS
California Civil Code Section § 1798.83 permits users of our website that are California residents to request certain information regarding our disclosure of personal information to third parties for their direct marketing purposes. If you are a California resident, you have the right to receive: a) information identifying any third-party companies to whom we may have disclosed, within the past year, personal information pertaining to you and your family for that company’s direct marketing purposes; and b) a description of the categories of personal information disclosed. Please send us an email with the subject line “Request for California Privacy Information” at the above address to obtain such information.
“DO NOT TRACK” SIGNALS
Do Not Track is a privacy preference you can set in your browser. When you turn on the Do Not Track, the browser sends a message to sites requesting them not to track the user. Currently, Procare does not respond to Do Not Track browser settings. In addition, Procare may use other technologies that are standard to the Internet to track visitors. Those tools may be used by us and by third parties to collect information about you and your internet activity, even if you have turned on Do Not Track. For information about Do Not Track, visit www.allaboutdnt.org.
CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
If this policy changes, we will notify you the next time you visit our site(s). You may review the current policy at any time by choosing the link labeled “Privacy Policy”.